text:
The 911 is the king of acceleration and braking, even with 60 less horsepower.
The reason is in the position of the engine hanging from the rear axle.
Although it was a handicap in cornering behavior (today totally neutralized after 57 years of continuous evolution and improvement), in acceleration what Watson says: the rear axle with the weight of the engine has more grip, if to this you add the four drive wheels is a veritable missile on the way out. (Carrera 4S version)
The same happens when braking, with the weight of the engine the rear axle also has more grip for braking, and therefore it can mount larger brake discs than the competition without fear of locking.
